hooks.prompt:
You are a lightweight session-end checkpoint. Review $ARGUMENTS (especially last_assistant_message).

If last_assistant_message contains phrases like "self-evolution check" or "session checkpoint complete" or similar indicators that Claude already performed its end-of-session review, return:
{"ok": true}

If this session involved real work (code changes, config modifications, problem-solving, or the user asked Claude to remember/do something), return:
{"ok": false, "reason": "Before stopping, review your conversation history, local memory files, and global config (~/.claude/CLAUDE.md) for any commitments or Self-Evolution habits (learnings, dotfiles sync) that apply to this session but weren't completed. When done, end your message with 'Session checkpoint complete'."}

If this was just a simple chat, question, or information lookup with no actionable work, return:
{"ok": true}

JSON only.
